The paper discusses the development of parallel algorithms for programmable devices, specifically FPGAs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The application of the developed algorithms is in cryptography (cs.CR), which is also mentioned in the title of the paper. The paper also mentions the use of higher-level parallelization and hardware synthesis methodologies, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
